This paper discusses the performance and generalization of deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also explores the concept of abstraction in DNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of DNNs for pattern recognition, specifically in image recognition tasks, is also discussed, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper mentions a computational neuroscience study, which relates to neural information processing (cs.NI).
